\f0\fs28 \cf0 BlastApp can use external level data files. The format of an external level data file is described below.\
\
Lines which start with 
\f1\b %
\f0\b0  are comments and are ignored.\
\
Every level is described in 5 lines:\
\
First line has a 
\f1\b +
\f0\b0  followed by the level name\
\
Second line has the level color, described as three floating point numbers between 0 and 1. These describe the red, green, and blue components of the level color. You can also specify "random" here to get a random color.\
\
Third line describes the ceiling height as letters between 
\f1\b a
\f0\b0  and 
\f1\b z
\f0\b0 . 
\f1\b z
\f0\b0  is the top of the game area, 
\f1\b a
\f0\b0  is the ground. You can have upto 151 letters to describe a game field with 150 "specs".\
\
Fourth line describes the ground height as letters between 
\f1\b a
\f0\b0  and 
\f1\b z
\f0\b0 . Clearly there should be enough room between the ceiling height and the ground height for the helicopter to pass through.\
\
Fifth line describes the enemy objects at each location:\
